### -------------------------------------------------------
### REST Client-style .http file for manual testing
###
### This file uses {{variable}} syntax that works with both
### REST Client and curl-code after importing environments
### from rest-client-settings.jsonc.
###
### Variables used here (host, apiKey, version, contentType)
### come from the imported environment + $shared merge.
###
### Manual test:
### 1. Copy rest-client-settings.jsonc content into VS Code
###    settings.json under "rest-client.environmentVariables"
### 2. Reload VS Code — import the environments when prompted
### 3. Set "local" as the active environment
### 4. Run each request below and verify the URL, headers,
###    and body are resolved correctly
### -------------------------------------------------------

@baseUrl = {{host}}/{{version}}

### List all users (environment vars + system vars)
GET {{baseUrl}}/users
Authorization: Bearer {{apiKey}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
User-Agent: {{userAgent}}
X-Request-Id: {{$guid}}

### Get a specific user
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/42
Authorization: Bearer {{apiKey}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
X-Timestamp: {{$timestamp}}

### Create a new user (with system variables in body)
POST {{baseUrl}}/users
Authorization: Bearer {{apiKey}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
    "id": "{{$guid}}",
    "name": "Jane Doe",
    "email": "jane@example.com",
    "role": "admin",
    "createdAt": "{{$datetime iso8601}}"
}

### Update a user
PUT {{baseUrl}}/users/42
Authorization: Bearer {{apiKey}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
    "name": "Jane Smith",
    "updatedAt": "{{$datetime iso8601}}"
}

### Delete a user
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/users/42
Authorization: Bearer {{apiKey}}
X-Request-Id: {{$guid}}

### Health check (no auth needed, uses only $shared vars)
GET {{host}}/health
User-Agent: {{userAgent}}

### System variables showcase (no environment needed)
GET https://httpbin.org/anything
X-Guid: {{$guid}}
X-Timestamp: {{$timestamp}}
X-Random: {{$randomInt 1 1000}}
X-Date-UTC: {{$datetime iso8601}}
X-Date-RFC: {{$datetime rfc1123}}
X-Date-Local: {{$localDatetime iso8601}}
X-Process-User: {{$processEnv USER}}

### DateTime offsets — timestamps relative to now
GET https://httpbin.org/anything
X-Yesterday: {{$datetime iso8601 -1 d}}
X-Tomorrow: {{$datetime iso8601 1 d}}
X-One-Hour-Ago: {{$timestamp -1 h}}
X-Next-Week: {{$datetime rfc1123 1 w}}
X-Thirty-Min-Ago-Local: {{$localDatetime iso8601 -30 m}}

### Prompt variables — interactive input at send time
# @prompt searchTerm What do you want to search for?
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/search?q={{%searchTerm}}
Authorization: Bearer {{apiKey}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

### Login with prompted credentials
# @prompt username
# @prompt password Your account password
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "username": "{{username}}",
    "password": "{{password}}"
}

### URL-encoded variables — {{%var}} percent-encodes the result
# Useful for query params with spaces or special characters
# @prompt query Search query
GET {{baseUrl}}/search?q={{%query}}&tag={{%apiKey}}
Authorization: Bearer {{apiKey}}
